  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting civilians during the implementation of Colombia&#x2019;s Peace Agreements</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Government and the international community in the aftermath of the country&apos;s plebiscite need to work closely with actors that have access to rural communities while  having the capacity to engage in a constructive process with different population groups. At the core of the Appeal is the importance of the accompaniment approach and Community Based Psychosocial Support (CBPS). Further, the local ecumenical actors in Colombia, supported by the global ecumenical actors, have a distinctive role and opportunity to take forward concrete action that will have an impact at the community level while also helping to influence country-level talks.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To build capacities on protection to reduce risks of violence for 7,000 most vulnerable people from 40
communities in or near FARC strongholds. In addition, provide psychosocial support to 1,050 people to develop coping mechanisms for emotional/psycho-social resilience.</narrative>
  </description>
